# logs/ (scratch)

`logs/` is scratch space for intermediate files and can be deleted at any time.

Rules:

- Put intermediate/working files here (not final deliverables).
- Use per-task subfolders: `logs/<short-desc>/<run-folder>/`.
- `run-folder` naming (local time): `YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-<epochMs>-<short-desc>`.
  - Example: `logs/subaru-brz-ads/20260301-212955-1709309395257-subaru-brz-ads/`.
- When you produce deliverables, create the matching folder under `artifacts/<short-desc>/<run-folder>/` with the exact same `run-folder` name.
- Each run folder must include a `README.md` that records progress and lists produced files.
- Keep `logs/AGENTS.md` tracked in git even if `logs/` is ignored.
